en_395458_0	Petroleum trade unions have halted trade union action over an oil pipeline dispute.
en_395458_1	It follows the talks the Trade Union had with Petroleum Minister Kabir Hashim.
en_395458_2	They have suspended the union action until next Friday night.
en_395458_3	The Petroleum Trade Unions Collective commenced union action demanding an immediate end to the balance work of the reconstruction of the fuel tunnel from the Colombo Port to the Kolonnawa terminal.
en_395458_4	Accordingly the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation trade unions halted the supply of fuel to the Ceylon Electricity Board from midnight yesterday.
en_395458_5	The Unions had a discussion with Minister Kabir Hashim today.
en_395458_6	The Minister gave the Unions an assurance that a resolution would be found to the issue after discussions at the Cabinet of Ministers tomorrow.
en_395458_7	Accordingly the Unions agreed to suspend their strike.
